<TITLE> India 177-2 at lunch </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 25 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh removed both openers as India moved to 177-2 at lunch on second day of the second and final Test at the Sher-e-Bangla National Stadium on Monday. Resuming on 69 without loss, the openers moved the score to 103 when Virender Sehwag was forced to fend off a snorter from Shahadat Hossain and was caught behind. He made 56 off 63 balls with eight fours. Gautam Gambhir (68) joined his partner back in the dressing after the left-hander was out in a similar manner to the bowling of Shafiul Islam half an hour before the break. Gambhir was trying to become the second batsman after the great Donald Bradman to score sixth consecutive Test hundreds. But he was surprised by a well-directed bouncer which had him jumping in the air before the ball looped towards the keeper. Rahul Dravid was batting on 33 and Sachin Tendulkar was 13 not out. Dravid was lucky to still be at the crease after getting the benefit of doubt when he was out of the crease at the non-striker's end while on nine and then being called back after getting caught off a Rubel Hossain no-ball. Bangladesh were all out for 233 in their first innings on Su
